Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{3}(chopped into 2cm pieces) (no need to peel) then place on a
large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle over a little @oil{to taste} then season with a pinch of
@salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer and roast on the top shelf of your oven until
golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

While the potatoes cook, cut the @broccoli{1}(cut into florets). Halve any
larger florets. Pop onto a separate lined baking tray.

Drizzle with oil, season with a pinch of salt and pepper then set aside.

Halve and peel the @onion{1/2}(halved and peeled). Chop half (double for 4p)
into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Finely chop the @parsley{5%g}(finely chopped) (stalks and all).

When the potatoes have 15 mins of cooking time left, roast the broccoli on the
middle shelf of the oven until crispy, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Add @flour{3%tbsp} (double for 4p) to a large #bowl{}. Season with a pinch of
salt and pepper. Mix together.

Lay the @pork loin steak{300%grams}(patted dry) in the bowl and turn to ensure
it gets an even coating of flour.

Repeat for the other pork loin steak(s).

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw pork and its packaging.

Place a large pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once the oil is hot, fry the pork loin steaks until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} on
each side. Lower heat to medium and fry for an additional ~{4-6%minutes}, turning
every ~{2%minutes}.

Once cooked, transfer the pork to a #plate{}, cover and allow to rest.

> IMPORTANT: Pork is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Return the pan to medium heat with a drizzle of oil.

Add the chopped onion and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic
and parsley and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Pour in the @red wine vinegar{1%sachet} and allow it to evaporate. Add
@water{75%ml} (double for 4p) and @chicken stock{1%sachet}.

Bring to the boil and stir to dissolve the stock.

Lower the heat and vigorously stir in @butter{2%tbsp} (double for 4p) until
melted and combined.

Remove the pan from the heat.

Serve the pork with the roast potatoes and crispy broccoli alongside.

Finish with a generous drizzle of the garlic butter sauce.